e^{\frac{x}{x+1}} = 1+ \frac{x}{x+1} + \frac1{2!} \left(\frac{x}{x+1} \right)^2 + \cdots < 1+ \frac{x}{x+1} + \left(\frac{x}{x+1}\right)^2 + \cdots = \frac1{1-\frac{x}{x+1}} = 1+x
f(x) \triangleq (1+x)\log(1+x)-x > 0
f'(x) = \log(1+x) > 0,\,\forall x>0
f(0) = 0
